  <rte>
    <name>Satterthwaite Bridge Circular</name>
    <desc>This short Lake District circular walk explores the area south of the village of Satterthwaite in Furness. The route passes through forest, visits an un-named tarn, continues beside waterfalls and rapids, and offers scenic interest throughout.</desc>
	<author>Copyright Walking Britain</author>
	<url>www.walkingbritain.co.uk/walk-3638-description</url>
